The TOI-674 Exoplanetary System


Overview

TOI-674 is a star with 0.42 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.42 times its radius. It is located 150.31 light years away from the solar system.

TOI-674 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the TOI-674 system


TOI-674 b

TOI-674 b was discovered by the Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite (TESS) observatory, in 2021-06, using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.03 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of TOI-674 b is 23.611 times the mass of Earth. The radius of TOI-674 b is 5.250 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, TOI-674 b is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system.
